# This tests that non-404 API errors from workspace/get-status are properly
# propagated to the user. Before the fix in WorkspaceFilesClient.Stat(),
# Stat() silently swallowed non-404 API errors, returning a zero-value
# wsfsFileInfo with nil error. Because wsfsFileInfo is a value type (not a
# pointer), filerFS.Open() didn't panic but treated the directory as a regular
# file (zero-value ObjectType makes IsDir() return false). The result was that
# export-dir silently reported success without exporting anything:
#
#   Exporting files from /test-dir
#   . -> <dir>/export (skipped; already exists)
#   Export complete
#
# After the fix, the 403 error is properly returned to the user.

mkdir -p "$TEST_TMP_DIR/export"
trace errcode $CLI workspace export-dir /test-dir "$TEST_TMP_DIR/export"
